            <h3>How does bontags work?</h3>
            <p>bontags works by downloading the hyper text of landing pages and then
            searching it for the keyword string.  The keyword can be some unique string
            appearing in your tags.</p>
            <br>
            <h3>How do I choose the keyword?</h3>
            <p>Let's suppose you wanted to test example.com and a bunch of other landing
            pages for the following doubleclick floodlight tags.
            <br>
            <br>
            <code>'https://example.fls.doubleclick.net/activityi;src=example;type=' +
            'dfg' +';cat=' + 'vbn' +';u1=' +'fdhv'+';ord=1;num=' + a + '?';</code>
            <br><br>
            You can use this full code line above as the keyword or some unique part of
            it that may suffice for validation purpose, for instance, <code>u1=' +'fdhv'+'</code>        
            </p>
            <br>
            <h3>Are multi-keyword queries supported?</h3>
            <p>No.  You'll have to run the test one keyword at a time.</p>
            <br>
            <h3>Can I export the results to Excel?</h3>
            <p>Yep! The results table can be copy-pasted in to Excel.</p>
